      A bytecode that writes a value into an element of an array.

      class  BranchingConstantComparisonBytecode
      A bytecode that compares the top element of the stack with a constant.
      class  BranchingNumericalComparisonBytecode
      A bytecode that applies a numerical comparison on the top two elements of the stack.
      class  CALL
      A bytecode that calls a method of a receiver.
      class  CAST
      A bytecode that casts the top of the stack into a given type.

      A bytecode that calls a constructor of an object.

      A bytecode that divides the top element of the stack by the underlying element.
      class  DUP
      A bytecode that duplicates the top element of the stack.

      A bytecode which checks if the top two elements of the stack are the same.
      class  FieldAccessBytecode
      A bytecode that accesses a field.
      class  FinalBytecode
      A bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language with no subsequent bytecode.

      A bytecode that checks if the one but last element of the stack is greater than or equal to its last element.
      class  GETFIELD
      A bytecode that reads the value of a given field of an object, called receiver.
      class  GT
      A bytecode that checks if the one but last element of the stack is greater than its last element.
      class  IF_CMPEQ
      A branching bytecode that compares the top two elements of the stack to check if they are the same.
      class  IF_CMPGE
      A comparison bytecode that compares the top two elements of the stack to check if the one but last is less than the top one.
      class  IF_CMPGT
      A comparison bytecode that compares the top two elements of the stack to check if the one but last is greater than the top one.
      class  IF_CMPLE
      A comparison bytecode that compares the top two elements of the stack to check if the one but last is less than or equal to the top one.
      class  IF_CMPLT
      A comparison bytecode that compares the top two elements of the stack to check if the one but last is less than the top one.
      class  IF_CMPNE
      A branching bytecode that compares the top two elements of the stack to check if they are the same.
      class  IF_FALSE
      A branching bytecode that checks if the top of the stack is the Boolean value false.
      class  IF_TRUE
      A branching bytecode that checks if the top of the stack is the Boolean value true.
      class  LE
      A bytecode that checks if the one but last element of the stack is less than or equal to its last element.
      class  LOAD
      A bytecode that loads the value of a local variable on top of the stack.
      class  LT
      A bytecode that checks if the one but last element of the stack is less than its last element.
      class  MUL
      A bytecode that multiplies the top two elements of the stack.
      class  NE
      A bytecode that checks if the top two elements of the stack are not the same.
      class  NEG
      A bytecode that negates the top element of the stack.
      class  NEW
      A bytecode that creates an object of a given class and pushes it on top of the stack.

      A bytecode that creates an array of a given type and size and then pushes on top of the stack a reference to that array.

      A bytecode that creates a string and pushes a reference to it on top of the stack.

      A bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language with one or no subsequent bytecode.

      A sequential bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language that does not call any piece of code.
      class  NOP
      A bytecode that does not do anything.

      A bytecode that performs a logical or operation on the top two elements of the stack.

      A bytecode that pops the top value of the stack.

      A bytecode that writes a value into a given field of an object, called receiver.
      class  RETURN
      A bytecode that terminates the execution of a method or constructor, and gives back the control to the caller.
      class  SequentialBytecode
      A sequential bytecode of the intermediate Kitten language, that is, a bytecode that never gives rise to a branching when executed and that has always a successor bytecode.
      class  STORE
      A bytecode that stores the top of the stack inside a local variable.

      A bytecode that subtracts the top element of the stack from the underlying element.
